column9:
I listen to Klezmer music (the musical tradition of the Jews of Europe) often. I find it entertaining and interesting. I will listen to some other instrumental music, like Jazz/Classical, for similar reasons, but I do so much less often. I often listen to Parno Graszt and Fanfare Ciocarlia, Hungarian and Romanian folk bands, respectively. 

I listen to some Ska music, especially revival bands such as The Specials, Madness, and The Selecter, because they're upbeat and fun. 

I listen to Calle Trece (puerto rican rap band) and some american rap music because the lyrics are fantastic. 

I listen to some vaporwave/Simpsonwave on occasion as part of an exercise in Accelerationist ideology.
